1
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:24,180
♪The breeze of the 1990s drifts by♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:27,180
♪Memories slowly flicker past♪

3
00:00:27,650 --> 00:00:31,430
♪My heartbeat
rises and falls with the tune♪

4
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,580
♪The story quietly begins here♪

5
00:00:35,330 --> 00:00:38,640
♪Under the dim lights, our eyes meet♪

6
00:00:38,710 --> 00:00:41,850
♪Time seems to stand still♪

7
00:00:42,350 --> 00:00:45,990
♪Your smile
breaks through the clouds like sun♪

8
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:49,150
♪Melting the snow deep in my heart♪

9
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:53,090
♪Street posters spread signals of love♪

10
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:56,110
♪Our story slowly begins to ferment♪

11
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:00,730
♪Hand in hand,
going through every dusk corner♪

12
00:01:00,930 --> 00:01:04,800
♪The taste of happiness is so subtle♪

13
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:08,740
♪Crossing back to the 1990s stage♪

14
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:12,480
♪You're my most beautiful surprise♪

15
00:01:12,790 --> 00:01:16,210
♪Love's flame burns within my heart♪

16
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,710
♪Not afraid of obstacles ahead♪

17
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:23,560
♪Sway with the rhythm.
Feel your heart pound♪

18
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:27,150
♪This love will never change♪

19
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:35,080
♪We hold tight in this crazy era♪

20
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:40,060
♪1990s love is what we rely on♪

21
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,070
=Once More Love in 1995=

22
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:44,937
=Episode 22=

23
00:01:45,921 --> 00:01:47,522
Aren't you good at fighting?

24
00:01:47,802 --> 00:01:48,962
Then why are you lying here?

25
00:01:50,481 --> 00:01:52,162
Zhou Zeyang is still at large,

26
00:01:52,321 --> 00:01:53,602
but you got hurt first.

27
00:02:05,401 --> 00:02:06,522
I'm sorry.

28
00:02:07,602 --> 00:02:09,001
You've helped me so many times,

29
00:02:09,001 --> 00:02:10,362
yet I never thanked you.

30
00:02:11,601 --> 00:02:14,482
I said I kept causing you trouble
for Shanshan,

31
00:02:14,482 --> 00:02:16,642
but I was settling a personal score.

32
00:02:17,522 --> 00:02:21,362
Old chap doesn't mean boss.
It means old man.

33
00:02:23,601 --> 00:02:25,482
I hated the future you

34
00:02:25,482 --> 00:02:26,561
and took it out on you now.

35
00:02:27,962 --> 00:02:31,401
I also stubbornly said
it's impossible between us.

36
00:02:32,841 --> 00:02:35,161
Falling for you was a real slap,

37
00:02:38,601 --> 00:02:40,401
but I couldn't help it.

38
00:02:50,802 --> 00:02:53,401
Hurry and wake up, will you?

39
00:02:54,001 --> 00:02:54,922
It's okay.

40
00:02:55,561 --> 00:02:56,642
It's not too late.

41
00:02:59,802 --> 00:03:01,082
You're okay?

42
00:03:02,001 --> 00:03:03,401
You scared me to death.

43
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:07,000
How could anything happen to me?

44
00:03:08,082 --> 00:03:09,681
I still want to be with you.

45
00:03:12,001 --> 00:03:13,522
Who said I'd be with you?

46
00:03:15,561 --> 00:03:17,561
I heard your confession clearly.

47
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:18,969
Don't even try to deny it.

48
00:03:32,601 --> 00:03:33,401
Alright.

49
00:03:36,121 --> 00:03:36,987
It's all over.

50
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:54,975
♪Rewind to 1995,
back to the street we met♪

51
00:03:55,112 --> 00:03:58,100
♪Wind blows through the mist
and leaves fall on your shoulder♪

52
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:01,800
♪I wish I could pause and stop time♪

53
00:04:01,887 --> 00:04:05,100
♪Let unspoken love
be preserved forever as amber♪

54
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:08,387
♪Rewind to 1995,
gentle touch of fingertips♪

55
00:04:08,437 --> 00:04:11,412
♪Star sparks in your eyes burn my chest♪

56
00:04:11,412 --> 00:04:15,362
♪This looping script
is beyond my saving♪

57
00:04:15,362 --> 00:04:20,037
♪I can only stay with you till the end
in this inverted hourglass♪

58
00:04:23,082 --> 00:04:23,762
Zhuang Shanshan.

59
00:04:24,522 --> 00:04:25,322
Tell me

60
00:04:25,462 --> 00:04:27,462
if you want to go to Juilliard School.

61
00:04:27,682 --> 00:04:28,962
Of course I do.

62
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,762
Then fill out the application form.

63
00:04:33,721 --> 00:04:35,082
Many major chances in life

64
00:04:35,082 --> 00:04:36,601
often only come once.

65
00:04:37,082 --> 00:04:37,882
And you?

66
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:39,601
You missed one before.

67
00:04:39,601 --> 00:04:41,202
Now you have a chance to make up for it.

68
00:04:41,481 --> 00:04:43,642
Don't you want to fight for it again?

69
00:04:57,882 --> 00:04:58,721
Yan.

70
00:04:59,481 --> 00:05:00,801
You've helped me so much.

71
00:05:01,362 --> 00:05:03,695
Even real family couldn't do this.

72
00:05:07,962 --> 00:05:08,935
I'm sorry.

73
00:05:12,325 --> 00:05:13,806
For pretending to be your cousin.

74
00:05:17,882 --> 00:05:20,122
I've long seen you as real family.

75
00:05:20,522 --> 00:05:22,841
Without you, I couldn't find myself.

76
00:05:25,841 --> 00:05:28,361
Don't you want to ask who I am?

77
00:05:30,721 --> 00:05:31,721
That's not important.

78
00:05:36,041 --> 00:05:38,322
Whether you're
Zhuang Yan or anyone else,

79
00:05:38,882 --> 00:05:40,481
I want to be family with you.

80
00:06:17,322 --> 00:06:18,322
What are you doing?

81
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,522
It's time to change the dressing.

82
00:06:20,522 --> 00:06:21,801
I'll help you change it.

83
00:06:25,481 --> 00:06:26,122
It's fine.

84
00:06:26,801 --> 00:06:27,921
I can do it myself.

85
00:06:29,882 --> 00:06:30,361
Embarrassed?

86
00:06:31,202 --> 00:06:31,841
Alright.

87
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:32,841
Do it yourself.

88
00:06:33,020 --> 00:06:33,990
The medical kit's here.

89
00:06:35,002 --> 00:06:36,082
Hey, wait.

90
00:06:37,281 --> 00:06:38,442
I thought about it.

91
00:06:38,921 --> 00:06:41,122
It's indeed easier if you help me.

92
00:06:51,801 --> 00:06:52,882
It's bleeding again.

93
00:06:57,921 --> 00:06:58,601
Does it hurt?

94
00:07:21,082 --> 00:07:22,202
It'll be done soon.

95
00:07:27,841 --> 00:07:29,882
Do you only stop fighting me

96
00:07:30,281 --> 00:07:31,481
when I'm hurt?

97
00:07:32,682 --> 00:07:34,361
I'm just using the time

98
00:07:34,762 --> 00:07:35,721
to treat you better.

99
00:07:37,082 --> 00:07:38,202
I don't want to be a player.

100
00:07:40,202 --> 00:07:41,401
What does that mean?

101
00:07:44,721 --> 00:07:45,921
You can think of it this way.

102
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:49,721
If one day I go back by accident,

103
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:51,882
wouldn't that mean
I used you and dumped you?

104
00:07:53,082 --> 00:07:54,522
Can you not go back then?

105
00:07:56,721 --> 00:07:58,322
That's not up to me.

106
00:07:58,481 --> 00:08:01,281
Just like I didn't come here
just because I wanted to.

107
00:08:06,650 --> 00:08:07,410
Zhuang Yan.

108
00:08:11,601 --> 00:08:13,122
Can you tell me about the future?

109
00:08:16,082 --> 00:08:17,882
The future between you and me.

110
00:08:20,841 --> 00:08:22,401
I'm sharp-tongued.

111
00:08:22,481 --> 00:08:24,921
Don't expect any nice words from me.

112
00:08:25,150 --> 00:08:27,450
You'll blame me for being rude later.

113
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:33,601
I want to hear it.

114
00:08:36,241 --> 00:08:37,481
Our first meeting

115
00:08:37,481 --> 00:08:38,601
wasn't nice at all.

116
00:08:40,042 --> 00:08:42,282
You showed up at my mom's grave,

117
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:43,574
said you were her brother

118
00:08:43,922 --> 00:08:45,082
and wanted to take me home.

119
00:08:46,282 --> 00:08:48,922
Then you took me to my dad's new family.

120
00:08:50,241 --> 00:08:51,481
My stepmom disliked me.

121
00:08:52,082 --> 00:08:54,042
My useless dad couldn't be bothered.

122
00:08:55,001 --> 00:08:56,641
You somehow became my guardian.

123
00:08:57,525 --> 00:08:59,082
You were very strict with me

124
00:08:59,082 --> 00:09:00,562
and were never nice to me.

125
00:09:01,312 --> 00:09:03,521
What you said to me the most was...

126
00:09:04,841 --> 00:09:06,082
Have you had enough?

127
00:09:07,082 --> 00:09:07,922
Anyway,

128
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,012
I really hated you as a kid.

129
00:09:14,082 --> 00:09:15,402
What about after you grew up?

130
00:09:17,121 --> 00:09:18,001
I hated you more.

131
00:09:22,521 --> 00:09:25,402
But you're very different now.

132
00:09:26,322 --> 00:09:28,841
After spending time with you lately,

133
00:09:31,841 --> 00:09:33,402
I don't hate you that much anymore.

134
00:09:41,082 --> 00:09:41,481
Qin Mo.

135
00:09:43,322 --> 00:09:44,641
Can you promise me

136
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:46,481
to always stay like this

137
00:09:46,922 --> 00:09:48,481
and not become that awful adult?

138
00:09:51,042 --> 00:09:51,562
Okay.

139
00:09:52,121 --> 00:09:52,922
I promise you.

140
00:10:01,481 --> 00:10:02,082
What?

141
00:10:05,442 --> 00:10:06,922
If you count it this way,

142
00:10:07,641 --> 00:10:09,162
shouldn't you call me Uncle?

143
00:10:10,442 --> 00:10:12,387
Look at you playing the elder card.

144
00:10:12,662 --> 00:10:14,241
You want some taboo romance with me?

145
00:10:14,881 --> 00:10:15,601
Forget it.

146
00:10:15,922 --> 00:10:16,521
Hey.

147
00:10:20,481 --> 00:10:22,322
I apologize on behalf of future Qin Mo.

148
00:10:24,202 --> 00:10:26,202
I'm sorry
I didn't give you a happy childhood.

149
00:10:28,121 --> 00:10:28,922
I promise

150
00:10:29,922 --> 00:10:32,001
nothing like that will happen again.

151
00:10:33,922 --> 00:10:35,601
And I won't allow your painful memories

152
00:10:37,721 --> 00:10:39,082
to happen again.

153
00:10:43,282 --> 00:10:45,082
Why are you trying to look cool
while hurt?

154
00:10:46,881 --> 00:10:49,082
I really don't mind where you came from.

155
00:10:49,802 --> 00:10:50,402
I know.

156
00:10:50,922 --> 00:10:52,042
You probably can't decide

157
00:10:52,042 --> 00:10:53,121
when you can go back.

158
00:10:53,912 --> 00:10:55,250
But I don't want your promise.

159
00:10:56,950 --> 00:10:58,881
I just want one clear answer from you.

160
00:11:00,442 --> 00:11:02,082
What clear answer?

161
00:11:24,725 --> 00:11:25,524
Zhuang Manying.

162
00:11:28,322 --> 00:11:29,481
At this very moment,

163
00:11:31,601 --> 00:11:32,641
will the future you

164
00:11:34,721 --> 00:11:36,402
marry the present me?

165
00:11:44,001 --> 00:11:46,001
If we don't know about the future,

166
00:11:47,282 --> 00:11:49,001
we should treasure the present more.

167
00:11:49,922 --> 00:11:51,481
I'm not sure what you like,

168
00:11:52,481 --> 00:11:54,121
but I can give you everything I have.

169
00:12:09,481 --> 00:12:11,402
Was my proposal too rushed?

170
00:12:18,282 --> 00:12:19,761
You won't accept it?

171
00:12:28,282 --> 00:12:29,601
What's the point of proposing?

172
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,361
Let's just get married.

173
00:12:38,912 --> 00:12:42,174
♪Crossing back to the 1990s stage♪

174
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:46,000
♪You're my most beautiful surprise♪

175
00:12:46,087 --> 00:12:49,887
♪Love's flame burns within my heart♪

176
00:12:49,975 --> 00:12:53,287
♪Not afraid of obstacles ahead♪

177
00:12:53,887 --> 00:12:57,450
♪Sway with the rhythm♪

178
00:12:57,562 --> 00:13:01,050
♪Feel your heart pound♪

179
00:13:19,337 --> 00:13:22,975
♪The old dial tone circles in my ear♪

180
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:26,412
♪Faded tickets point to a cicada summer♪

181
00:13:26,575 --> 00:13:30,162
♪The videotape
whispers your image in the frame♪

182
00:13:30,462 --> 00:13:33,750
♪Against the light, the plaid shirt
reveals a clear and transparent smile♪

183
00:13:33,975 --> 00:13:37,600
♪I'm a clumsy guest in a frozen scene♪

184
00:13:37,762 --> 00:13:41,100
♪How do I answer familiar lines?♪

185
00:13:41,175 --> 00:13:44,887
♪I know
the train will leave this station♪

186
00:13:44,937 --> 00:13:48,800
♪I know the ending's in a faded future♪

187
00:13:48,862 --> 00:13:54,912
♪Yet I want to approach that warmth♪

188
00:13:56,087 --> 00:14:02,825
♪Even one second rewrites missed lines♪

189
00:14:03,112 --> 00:14:07,387
♪Rewind to 1995,
back to the street we met♪

190
00:14:07,387 --> 00:14:10,687
♪Wind blows through the sycamore leaves
and lands on your shoulder♪

191
00:14:10,762 --> 00:14:15,062
♪I wish I could pause and stop time♪

192
00:14:15,125 --> 00:14:18,775
♪Let unspoken love
be preserved forever as amber♪

193
00:14:18,775 --> 00:14:22,337
♪Rewind to 1995,
gentle touch of fingertips♪

194
00:14:22,387 --> 00:14:25,650
♪Star sparks in your eyes burn my chest♪

195
00:14:25,650 --> 00:14:29,400
♪This looping script
is beyond my saving♪

196
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:36,112
♪I can only stay with you till the end
in this inverted hourglass♪
